<br>
It sounds a lot like you're having driver issues. A few notes to consider:<br>
<br>
Newer is almost always better.<br>
<br>
Never. Ever. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> EVER</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> use distributor proprietary drivers. If it doesn't come directly from ATI, don't use it. Go <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://support.ati.com/issuetype/driverdirect.html?parent=0&amp;folder=72&amp;doc=57">Here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for ATI's driver section.<br>
<br>
If that doesn't work, here are a few things you could try:<br>
<br>
Go into your card's advanced settings (this is usually under display properties) and do the following:<br>
<br>
•  Enable VSync. This could be the root of the screen flicker issue you're experiencing<br>
•  If VSync is already enabled, disable it. Oddly this could <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> also</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be the causing the flicker problem <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
•  Disable texture compression. If you can't find an option to do this, then look for a &quot;quality versus performance&quot; slider of some sort and tilt it a few notches toward &quot;quality&quot;. This could be what's causing the purple trees.<br>
<br>
I'm afraid that's all I can think of for now. Let me know how it turns out. Good luck to ya <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><IMG SRC="http://members.bellatlantic.net/vze24qqk/public_html/marasig.jpg" ALT="I am the Dragon of Blood, a relentless prince of pain..." BORDER="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/binfinitusvindicat.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=darkhealer>Darkhealer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/4/02 5:28:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=588.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ATI Radeon 8500: Help!</span><hr size=1> Thank for the info... I'll try the settings. (I think I've already tried the Vsink one, but I'll check again)... I'm currently using the newest ati drivers, however they're still in beta =\...   guess I'll go tinker some more and see how things turn out.<br>
