<br>
Often times for the sake of simplicity (programmers, go figure) beta drivers will have a few known compatibility problems.<br>
<br>
A few other things to check:<br>
<br>
Did you upgrade from a PCI video card to an AGP (or vice-versa)? Go into your BIOS settings and make sure the slot that your new video card is plugged into is configured correctly!<br>
<br>
Of course, if all else fails, E-MAIL ATI! heh. <p><IMG SRC="http://members.bellatlantic.net/vze24qqk/public_html/marasig.jpg" ALT="I am the Dragon of Blood, a relentless prince of pain..." BORDER="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/binfinitusvindicat.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=arciteizuber>Arcite iz uber</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/6/02 11:45:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=588.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ATI Radeon 8500: Help!</span><hr size=1> The flickering is just your moniter's refresh rate.<br>
